142 and 211**: Capable of MIG/flux-cored welding.\\n- **Multimatic 215 and 220 AC/DC**: Capable of MIG/flux-cored, DC stick, and DC TIG welding. The Multimatic 220 AC/DC also supports AC TIG welding.\\n\\n**Welding Capability:**\\n- **Mild and Stainless Steel**: Both Millermatic models can weld from a minimum of 24 gauge to a maximum of 3/16 inch. Multimatic models can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch.\\n- **Aluminum**: Millermatic 142 can weld from 18 gauge to 14 gauge, while Millermatic 211 can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch. Multimatic models can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch.\\n\\n**Power:**\\n- **Millermatic 142**: Input power of 120 V with an amperage range of 30-140 A.\\n- **Millermatic 211**: Input power of 120/240 V with an amperage range of 30-230 A.\\n- **Multimatic 215 and 220 AC/DC**: Input power of 120/240 V with an amperage range of 20-230 A.\\n\\n**Features:**\\n- **Millermatic 211**: Includes Auto-Set\\u2122 and MVP\\u2122.\\n- **Multimatic 215**: Includes Auto-Set\\u2122, MVP\\u2122, and a color LCD display.\\n- **Multimatic 220 AC/DC**: Includes Auto-Set\\u2122, MVP\\u2122, a color LCD display, QuickTech\\u2122, Pro-Set\\u2122, and TIG high-frequency starts.", "usage": {"prompt_tokens": 2915, "completion_tokens": 386, "total_tokens": 3301, "total_cost_usd": 0.0111475}}]
