 Kit 301439 For HWY-Mid Frame and HWY-225. Replacement fenders.\\n\\nHWY-Mid Frame Trailer 301438 For Bobcat, Trailblazer and Big Blue 400 Pro/ Dual Hitch 301441\\n\\n400 PipePro/450 Duo CST. A 646 kg (1,424 Ib.) For HWY-Mid Frame and capacity highway trailer with welded steel tubing HWY-225. Combination\\n\\nframe, heavy-duty axle with roller bearing hubs 50 mm (2 in.) ball hitch and leaf-spring suspension. Includes jack stand, and 76 mm (3 in.) l"}, {"source": "2024-int-catalog-Miller-Products.pdf", "doc_id": 32, "file_id": "1SZK4gC7R04nMtyK556SpCPid5WoH2uCL", "page": 4, "total_pages": 104, "collection": "banditosinc", "snippet": "2 5\\n\\nMillermatic 142\\n\\nMild Steel Welding Capability 9.5 mm (3/8 in.)\\n\\nMax.\\n\\nMin. 0.6 mm (24 ga.) 0.6 mm (24 ga.)\\n\\n4.8 mm (3/16 in.)\\n\\nAluminum Welding Capability 9.5 mm (3/8 in.)\\n\\nMax.\\n\\n1.9 mm (14 ga.) I a\\n\\nMin. | 4,2 mm (18 ga.) 1.2 mm (18 ga.)\\n\\nAluminum welding with the Millermatic 142 or Millermatic 211 uses optional Spoolmate 100 spool gun with 4043 aluminum series wire OR optional Spoolmate 150 spool gun with 4000 or 5000 series aluminum wire.\\n\\nRecommended aluminum solution\\n\\nSpoolmate 100 OR"}], "answer": "The comparison of small frame Millermatic\\u00ae and Multimatic\\u00ae models is as follows:\\n\\n**Processes and Capabilities:**\\n- **Millermatic 142 and 211**: Capable of MIG/flux-cored welding.\\n- **Multimatic 215 and 220 AC/DC**: Capable of MIG/flux-cored, DC stick, and DC TIG welding. The Multimatic 220 AC/DC also supports AC TIG welding.\\n\\n**Welding Capability:**\\n- **Mild and Stainless Steel**: Both Millermatic models can weld from a minimum of 24 gauge to a maximum of 3/16 inch. Multimatic models can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch.\\n- **Aluminum**: Millermatic 142 can weld from 18 gauge to 14 gauge, while Millermatic 211 can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch. Multimatic models can weld from 24 gauge to 3/8 inch.\\n\\n**Power:**\\n- **Millermatic 142**: Input power of 120 V